==Spanish==
===Etymology===
According to the Spanish Wiktionary, ''chingar'' is a corruption of ''[[tiznar]]''.  The Real Academia Española, however, says it comes from the [[Caló]] word ''[[čingarár]]'', meaning ''to [[fight]]''.

===Verb===
'''chingar'''

# (''Mexico'') To [[bother]]
# (''Mexico'') To engage in [[sexual intercourse]]
# (''Mexico'') To be wrong; to [[screw up]]
# (''Mexico'') To [[steal]]

'''chingarle'''
# (''Mexico'') To [[work]] hard

